issue.title: Bump spring.version from 5.3.9 to 5.3.10
issue.body:
Bumps `spring.version` from 5.3.9 to 5.3.10. Updates `spring-test` from 5.3.9 to 5.3.10
Release notes

Sourced from [spring-test's releases](https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/releases).

v5.3.10

:star: New Features

  • Invalid JavaBean property 'logoutHandlers' being accessed (warning in the logs for Spring Security's ConcurrentSessionFilter) [#27372](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/27372)
  • Convenient configuration of type permissions for XStream 1.4.18 [#27343](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/27343)
  • Add SmallRye Mutiny support to ReactiveAdapterRegistry [#27331](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/pull/27331)
  • Introduce ExceptionCollector testing utility [#27316](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/27316)
  • Support TimeUnit in the @Scheduled annotation [#27309](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/pull/27309)
  • Make it possible to determine if circular references are prohibited or if the cycle just couldn't be broken [#27289](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/27289)
  • Support Charset for character encoding in MockMvc [#27231](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/27231)
  • Support default character encoding for response in MockMvc [#27230](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/27230)
  • Introduce setDefaultCharacterEncoding() in MockHttpServletResponse [#27214](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/27214)
  • Use MessageSource for @ExceptionHandler methods [#27203](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/pull/27203)
  • ResponseStatusException.initCause always throws IllegalStateException [#27196](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/27196)
  • Introduce soft assertions for WebTestClient [#26969](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/pull/26969)
  • Introduce soft assertions for MockMvc [#26917](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/pull/26917)
  • Blockhound flags a blocking call when WebFlux serves a static resource [#26631](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/26631)
  • Optimize memory allocations in StringUtils#cleanPath [#26316](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/pull/26316)
  • InvocableHandlerMethod calls makeAccessible(getBridgedMethod()) on every call [SPR-15230] [#19795](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/19795)

:lady_beetle: Bug Fixes

  • Support char, float, and double primitive default values in BeanUtils.instantiateClass() [#27390](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/pull/27390)
  • Fix memory leak on AOP Proxy class definition cache [#27375](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/pull/27375)
  • Fix response body missing 1st byte inside UnknownContentTypeException [#27374](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/pull/27374)
  • CommonsMultipartResolver and DEBUG logging lead to empty fileMap in MultipartHttpServletRequest [#27350](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/27350)
  • Fix UrlPathHelper#shouldRemoveSemicolonContent() [#27303](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/pull/27303)
  • CompositeUriComponentsContributor#hasContributors: method name is not compliant with its intention [#27271](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/27271)
  • Error with formatMapping method in AbstractMethodMessageHandler.java [#27247](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/27247)
  • Apply default ResultHandlers before default ResultMatchers in MockMvc [#27225](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/27225)
  • MockHttpServletResponse.characterEncoding should not be @Nullable [#27219](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/27219)
  • WebSocketMessageBrokerStats.getExecutorStatsInfo() throws exception if Executor is not a ThreadPoolExecutor [#27209](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/27209)
  • HtmlUnitRequestBuilder ignores file uploaded via HtmlFileInput.setData() [#27199](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/27199)

:notebook_with_decorative_cover: Documentation

  • Fix wording in Javadoc of ClientResponse.mutate() [#27389](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/pull/27389)
  • Fix some typos and mistakes in docs [#27388](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/pull/27388)
  • Fix misplaced comma in AOP doc [#27387](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/pull/27387)
  • Fix Kotlin example for filtering handler functions [#27337](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/pull/27337)
  • Document when prepareTestInstance() is invoked when using the SpringMethodRule [#27305](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/27305)
  • Fix duplicated "the" occurrences in Javadoc and XSD [#27291](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/pull/27291)
  • Fix typo in DefaultPartHttpMessageReader [#27260](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/pull/27260)
  • Fix reference to Optional.isPresent() in ObjectUtils.isEmpty() [#27223](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/pull/27223)
  • Clarify that ClientRequest.from(..) also copies body [#27220](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/pull/27220)
  • @Cacheable caches empty Optionals but documentation states otherwise [#27184](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/27184)
  • Reference docs missing left-hand side navigation [#27177](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/27177)

:hammer: Dependency Upgrades

... (truncated)

Commits
  • 21c3b51 Release v5.3.10
  • aa14c24 Migrate to Spring Builds account
  • 4c720ea Fix GitHub credentials to use token rather than password
  • 2d65bce Polish Eclipse IDE support
  • b8b85a6 Defensive handling of dimensions nullability
  • 3baaced Alignment with other abstract utils classes
  • 4322ee1 Polish Eclipse IDE support
  • 3faf445 Re-enable import into Eclipse IDE
  • 9e986c0 Polish ide.gradle
  • f07e6a1 Support char primitive default values in BeanUtils.instantiateClass()
  • Additional commits viewable in [compare view](https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/compare/v5.3.9...v5.3.10)

:star: New Features

  • Invalid JavaBean property 'logoutHandlers' being accessed (warning in the logs for Spring Security's ConcurrentSessionFilter) [#27372](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/27372)
  • Convenient configuration of type permissions for XStream 1.4.18 [#27343](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/27343)

  • Support TimeUnit in the @Scheduled annotation [#27309](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/pull/27309)
  • Make it possible to determine if circular references are prohibited or if the cycle just couldn't be broken [#27289](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/27289)
